    "course_title": "FROM ATOMS TO MOLECULES",
    "description": "Topics covered include protein structure and folding, protein dynamics, biological catalysis, membrane structure and assembly, nucleic acid structure and folding, and bioenergetics. Each topic includes discussion of the primary literature, hypothesis generation, experimental design, data, analysis and interpretation underlying the facts in the textbook.  Supports transition from undergraduate consumers of knowledge to graduate students and future independent scientists who will discover and add new knowledge.",
